Interpret the method to pass the information between pages in PHP with an example.
Using GET Method
Page 1 (form.html):
<!-- Sends data via URL -->
<form action="page2.php" method="get">
 Name: <input type="text" name="username">
 <input type="submit" value="Submit">
</form>
Page 2 (page2.php):
<?php
$name = $_GET['username'];
echo "Hello, $name!";
?>
Using POST Method
Page 1 (form.html):
<!-- Sends data secretly (not in URL) -->
<form action="page2.php" method="post">
 Email: <input type="email" name="email">
 <input type="submit" value="Send">
</form>
Page 2 (page2.php):
<?php
$email = $_POST['email'];
echo "Your email is: $email";
?>
